   zobra is a Zig port of cobra. APIs, structural design, hook
   ordering, and behaviour are emulated; ideas and APIs are not
   copyrightable and need no attribution. The following limited
   passages are verbatim or near-verbatim copies of cobra/pflag
   strings and are derivative under Apache 2.0:

   (a) pflag-byte-identical error wording in the parse / coerce path.
       Format strings:
         "invalid argument \"%s\" for \"--%s\" flag: %s"
         "invalid argument \"%s\" for \"-%c, --%s\" flag: %s"
         "unknown flag: --%s"
         "unknown shorthand flag: \"%s\" in -%s"
         "flag needs an argument: --%s"
         "flag needs an argument: \"%s\" in -%s"
         "bad flag syntax: %s"
       The pflag-shaped strconv function names also appear verbatim
       as `func` arguments routed through the error renderer:
         "ParseBool", "ParseInt", "ParseUint", "ParseFloat", "Atoi"
       Sites in zobra:
         src/core/flag/bind.zig (failCoerce / failCoerceWithRendered)
         src/core/command/parse_diag.zig (render)

   (b) cobra-byte-identical flag-group violation wording. Format
       strings:
         "if any flags in the group [%s] are set they must all be
          set; missing [%s]"
         "at least one of the flags in the group [%s] is required"
         "if any flags in the group [%s] are set none of the others
          can be; [%s] were all set"
       Sites in zobra:
         src/core/command/groups.zig

   (c) Verbatim Long-text wording of the auto-injected `help` and
       `completion` subcommands, mirroring cobra's
       `AddDefaultHelpCmd` and `initDefaultCompletionCmd`:
         "Help about any command"
         "Help provides help for any command in the application."
         "Generate shell completion scripts"
         "Generate shell completion scripts. To load completions: …"
       Sites in zobra:
         src/core/command/defaults.zig
         src/completion/runtime.zig

   What is NOT derivative of cobra:
   - The shell-completion script templates in src/completion/
     {bash,zsh,fish,powershell}.zig. These are zobra-original
     minimum-viable scripts that follow cobra's wire protocol but do
     not vendor cobra's bundled completion scripts. If a future
     release vendors cobra's scripts byte-for-byte, this notice will
     be extended and a strip-on-render banner mechanism added (cf.
     vipvot's approach in its NOTICE).
   - The `oracle/` directory contains a Go program built against
     spf13/cobra and spf13/pflag for differential testing. It is a
     build-time test artefact, not part of zobra's distributed
     source (excluded from build.zig.zon's `paths`).
